{"id": "EUVD-2024-50471", "enisaUuid": "e9dcd529-8457-3079-9338-272cfd5186bd", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nwifi: iwlwifi: mvm: fix 6 GHz scan construction\n\nIf more than 255 colocated APs exist for the set of all\nAPs found during 2.4/5 GHz scanning, then the 6 GHz scan\nconstruction will loop forever since the loop variable\nhas type u8, which can never reach the number found when\nthat's bigger than 255, and is stored in a u32 variable.\nAlso move it into the loops to have a smaller scope.\n\nUsing a u32 there is fine, we limit the number of APs in\nthe scan list and each has a limit on the number of RNR\nentries due to the frame size. With a limit of 1000 scan\nresults, a frame size upper bound of 4096 (really it's\nmore like ~2300) and a TBTT entry size of at least 11,\nwe get an upper bound for the number of ~372k, well in\nthe bounds of a u32.", "datePublished": "2024-11-19T17:19:39", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-03T22:28:49", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2ac15e5a8f42fed5d90ed9e1197600913678c50f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cde8a7eb5c6762264ff0f4433358e0a0d250c875", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/fc621e7a043de346c33bd7ae7e2e0c651d6152ef", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/2ccd5badadab2d586e91546bf5af3deda07fef1f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7245012f0f496162dd95d888ed2ceb5a35170f1a", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-53055", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/01/msg00001.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53055"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "09833fd4-992e-3578-9be7-f48959712002", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12"}, {"id": "13e76313-a662-3623-a099-d74cfcaf6056", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "eae94cf82d7456b57fa9fd55c1edb8a726dcc19c <2ac15e5a8f42fed5d90ed9e1197600913